The paper deals with the representation of graphs using obstacles on a grid, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of obstacle representation is also related to graph theory (cs.DM) and the study of planar graphs (cs.DS). The paper also discusses NP-hardness results, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC) and the study of graph algorithms (cs.GT).
